Suspected members of Ansaru and Boko Haram terror groups have abducted many travellers and set eight vehicles ablaze on Birnin Gwari-Kaduna Road. A source said the gunmen also intercepted a convoy of vehicles with security escorts during the attack, which took place on Tuesday. An association, Birnin-Gwari Vanguard for Security and Good Governance, said the attack was the fourth in days. Police spokesman Muhammad Jalige said he would first “contact the Area Commander in charge of the area” before getting back to our correspondent.   Nigeria, 28 others push anti-piracy, oil theft resolutions     Buhari lauds Okpaleke’s appointment as fourth Catholic…     Yoruba global summit series to begin June 11   But in a statement, Chairman of Birnin-Gwari Vanguard, Ibrahim Abubakar Nagwari, said the incident happened between Kuriga and Manini near Udawa. “It is evidently clear that bandits and Ansaru (Boko Haram) have declared total war on our people, yet the political will by the authorities to honour their oaths of office to protect lives and property of our citizens remains a mirage. “On Tuesday, terrorists along Birnin-Gwari-Kaduna Highway intercepted a convoy of motorists with security escorts. In the last four days terrorists laid siege on motorists on Birnin-Gwari-Kaduna Highway. “Today, eight vehicles were set ablaze by the terrorists, while a number of innocent commuters, mostly women and children, were taken into the bush by the terrorists,” Nagwari said.